>>What is the boiling temperature of water in Celcius?||You can convert Fahrenheit to Celcius with the following forumula: \(C = (F-32)*5/9\).<<
[[
32&#176; {{Burr!:: 3232&#176; is the temperature at which water freezes in Fahrenheit}}
212&#176; {{Almost:: 212&#176; is the termperature at which water boils in Fahrenheit}}
(100&#176;) {{Correct, water boils at 100&#176; Celcius}}
451&#176; {{Ouch!!:: Paper is reported to auto ignite at 451&#176; Fahrenheit}}
]]

||212&#176; is the correct temperature, as specified in Fahrenheit||
||32&#176; is too cold using either methods of specification||

[explanation]
Temperatures in Celcius are much more logical than Fahrenheit temperatures. Water freezes at 0&#176; and boils at 100&#176;. 
